52 static bool sameStringIgnoringWS(const std::string& s1, const std::string& s2)
53 {
54  unsigned int i1 = 0;
55  unsigned int i2 = 0;
56  while (i1 < s1.size() && isspace(s1[i1]))
57  i1++;
58  while (i2 < s2.size() && isspace(s2[i2]))
59  i2++;
60  while (i1 < s1.size() && i2 < s2.size())
61  {
62  if (i1 < s1.size() && i2 < s2.size())
63  {
64  if (s1[i1] != s2[i2])
65  return false;
66  i1++;
67  i2++;
68  }
69  while (i1 < s1.size() && isspace(s1[i1]))
70  i1++;
71  while (i2 < s2.size() && isspace(s2[i2]))
72  i2++;
73  }
74  return i1 == s1.size() && i2 == s2.size();
75 }
76 static void expect_near(const Eigen::MatrixXd& x, const Eigen::MatrixXd& y,
77  double eps = std::numeric_limits<double>::epsilon())
78 {
79  ASSERT_EQ(x.rows(), y.rows());
80  ASSERT_EQ(x.cols(), y.cols());
81  for (int r = 0; r < x.rows(); ++r)
82  for (int c = 0; c < x.cols(); ++c)
83  EXPECT_NEAR(x(r, c), y(r, c), eps) << "(r,c) = (" << r << "," << c << ")";
84 }

86 // clang-format off
87 #define EXPECT_NEAR_TRACED(...) { \
88  SCOPED_TRACE("expect_near(" #__VA_ARGS__ ")"); \
89  expect_near(__VA_ARGS__); \
90 }

93 TEST(Loading, SimpleRobot)
94 {
95  moveit::core::RobotModelBuilder builder("myrobot", "base_link");
96  builder.addVirtualJoint("odom_combined", "base_link", "floating", "base_joint");
97  ASSERT_TRUE(builder.isValid());
98  moveit::core::RobotModelPtr model = builder.build();
99  moveit::core::RobotState state(model);
100 
101  state.setToDefaultValues();
102 
103  // make sure that this copy constructor works
104  moveit::core::RobotState new_state(state);
105 
106  EXPECT_EQ(new_state.getVariablePosition("base_joint/rot_w"), 1.0);
107 
108  EXPECT_EQ(std::string("myrobot"), model->getName());
109  EXPECT_EQ((unsigned int)7, new_state.getVariableCount());
110 
111  const std::vector<moveit::core::LinkModel*>& links = model->getLinkModels();
112  EXPECT_EQ((unsigned int)1, links.size());
113 
114  const std::vector<moveit::core::JointModel*>& joints = model->getJointModels();
115  EXPECT_EQ((unsigned int)1, joints.size());
116 
117  const std::vector<std::string>& pgroups = model->getJointModelGroupNames();
118  EXPECT_EQ((unsigned int)0, pgroups.size());
119 }

121 TEST(LoadingAndFK, SimpleRobot)
122 {
123  moveit::core::RobotModelBuilder builder("myrobot", "base_link");
124  geometry_msgs::Pose pose;
125  tf2::toMsg(tf2::Vector3(-0.1, 0, 0), pose.position);
126  tf2::Quaternion q;
127  q.setRPY(0, 0, -1);
128  pose.orientation = tf2::toMsg(q);
129  builder.addCollisionBox("base_link", { 1, 2, 1 }, pose);
130  tf2::toMsg(tf2::Vector3(0, 0, 0), pose.position);
131  q.setRPY(0, 0, 0);
132  pose.orientation = tf2::toMsg(q);
133  builder.addVisualBox("base_link", { 1, 2, 1 }, pose);
134  tf2::toMsg(tf2::Vector3(0, 0.099, 0), pose.position);
135  q.setRPY(0, 0, 0);
136  pose.orientation = tf2::toMsg(q);
137  builder.addInertial("base_link", 2.81, pose, 0.1, -0.2, 0.5, -0.09, 1, 0.101);
138  builder.addVirtualJoint("odom_combined", "base_link", "planar", "base_joint");
139  builder.addGroup({}, { "base_joint" }, "base");
140 
141  ASSERT_TRUE(builder.isValid());
142  moveit::core::RobotModelPtr model = builder.build();
143  moveit::core::RobotState state(model);
144 
145  EXPECT_EQ((unsigned int)3, state.getVariableCount());
146 
147  state.setToDefaultValues();
148 
149  EXPECT_EQ((unsigned int)1, (unsigned int)model->getJointModelCount());
150  EXPECT_EQ((unsigned int)3, (unsigned int)model->getJointModels()[0]->getLocalVariableNames().size());
151 
152  std::map<std::string, double> joint_values;
153  joint_values["base_joint/x"] = 10.0;
154  joint_values["base_joint/y"] = 8.0;
155 
156  // testing incomplete state
157  std::vector<std::string> missing_states;
158  state.setVariablePositions(joint_values, missing_states);
159  ASSERT_EQ(missing_states.size(), 1u);
160  EXPECT_EQ(missing_states[0], std::string("base_joint/theta"));
161  joint_values["base_joint/theta"] = 0.1;
162 
163  state.setVariablePositions(joint_values, missing_states);
164  ASSERT_EQ(missing_states.size(), 0u);
165 
166  EXPECT_NEAR_TRACED(state.getGlobalLinkTransform("base_link").translation(), Eigen::Vector3d(10, 8, 0));
167 
168  state.setVariableAcceleration("base_joint/x", 0.0);
169 
170  // making sure that values get copied
171  moveit::core::RobotState* new_state = new moveit::core::RobotState(state);
172  EXPECT_NEAR_TRACED(state.getGlobalLinkTransform("base_link").translation(), Eigen::Vector3d(10, 8, 0));
173  delete new_state;
174 
175  std::vector<double> jv(state.getVariableCount(), 0.0);
176  jv[state.getRobotModel()->getVariableIndex("base_joint/x")] = 5.0;
177  jv[state.getRobotModel()->getVariableIndex("base_joint/y")] = 4.0;
178  jv[state.getRobotModel()->getVariableIndex("base_joint/theta")] = 0.0;
179 
180  state.setVariablePositions(jv);
181  EXPECT_NEAR_TRACED(state.getGlobalLinkTransform("base_link").translation(), Eigen::Vector3d(5, 4, 0));
182 }

377 TEST_F(OneRobot, FK)
378 {
379  moveit::core::RobotModelConstPtr model = robot_model_;
380 
381  // testing that the two planning groups are the same
382  const moveit::core::JointModelGroup* g_one = model->getJointModelGroup("base_from_joints");
383  const moveit::core::JointModelGroup* g_two = model->getJointModelGroup("base_from_base_to_tip");
384  const moveit::core::JointModelGroup* g_three = model->getJointModelGroup("base_with_subgroups");
385  const moveit::core::JointModelGroup* g_four = model->getJointModelGroup("base_with_bad_subgroups");
386  const moveit::core::JointModelGroup* g_mim = model->getJointModelGroup("mim_joints");
387 
388  ASSERT_TRUE(g_one != nullptr);
389  ASSERT_TRUE(g_two != nullptr);
390  ASSERT_TRUE(g_three != nullptr);
391  ASSERT_TRUE(g_four == nullptr);
392 
393  // joint_b is a fixed joint, so no one should have it
394  ASSERT_EQ(g_one->getJointModelNames().size(), 3u);
395  ASSERT_EQ(g_two->getJointModelNames().size(), 3u);
396  ASSERT_EQ(g_three->getJointModelNames().size(), 4u);
397  ASSERT_EQ(g_mim->getJointModelNames().size(), 2u);
398 
399  // only the links in between the joints, and the children of the leafs
400  ASSERT_EQ(g_one->getLinkModelNames().size(), 3u);
401  // g_two only has three links
402  ASSERT_EQ(g_two->getLinkModelNames().size(), 3u);
403  ASSERT_EQ(g_three->getLinkModelNames().size(), 4u);
404 
405  std::vector<std::string> jmn = g_one->getJointModelNames();
406  std::sort(jmn.begin(), jmn.end());
407  EXPECT_EQ(jmn[0], "base_joint");
408  EXPECT_EQ(jmn[1], "joint_a");
409  EXPECT_EQ(jmn[2], "joint_c");
410  jmn = g_two->getJointModelNames();
411  std::sort(jmn.begin(), jmn.end());
412  EXPECT_EQ(jmn[0], "base_joint");
413  EXPECT_EQ(jmn[1], "joint_a");
414  EXPECT_EQ(jmn[2], "joint_b");
415  jmn = g_three->getJointModelNames();
416  std::sort(jmn.begin(), jmn.end());
417  EXPECT_EQ(jmn[0], "base_joint");
418  EXPECT_EQ(jmn[1], "joint_a");
419  EXPECT_EQ(jmn[2], "joint_b");
420  EXPECT_EQ(jmn[3], "joint_c");
421 
422  // but they should have the same links to be updated
423  ASSERT_EQ(g_one->getUpdatedLinkModels().size(), 6u);
424  ASSERT_EQ(g_two->getUpdatedLinkModels().size(), 6u);
425  ASSERT_EQ(g_three->getUpdatedLinkModels().size(), 6u);
426 
427  EXPECT_EQ(g_one->getUpdatedLinkModels()[0]->getName(), "base_link");
428  EXPECT_EQ(g_one->getUpdatedLinkModels()[1]->getName(), "link_a");
429  EXPECT_EQ(g_one->getUpdatedLinkModels()[2]->getName(), "link_b");
430  EXPECT_EQ(g_one->getUpdatedLinkModels()[3]->getName(), "link_c");
431 
432  EXPECT_EQ(g_two->getUpdatedLinkModels()[0]->getName(), "base_link");
433  EXPECT_EQ(g_two->getUpdatedLinkModels()[1]->getName(), "link_a");
434  EXPECT_EQ(g_two->getUpdatedLinkModels()[2]->getName(), "link_b");
435  EXPECT_EQ(g_two->getUpdatedLinkModels()[3]->getName(), "link_c");
436 
437  EXPECT_EQ(g_three->getUpdatedLinkModels()[0]->getName(), "base_link");
438  EXPECT_EQ(g_three->getUpdatedLinkModels()[1]->getName(), "link_a");
439  EXPECT_EQ(g_three->getUpdatedLinkModels()[2]->getName(), "link_b");
440  EXPECT_EQ(g_three->getUpdatedLinkModels()[3]->getName(), "link_c");
441 
442  // bracketing so the state gets destroyed before we bring down the model
443 
444  moveit::core::RobotState state(model);
445 
446  EXPECT_EQ((unsigned int)7, state.getVariableCount());
447 
448  state.setToDefaultValues();
449 
450  std::map<std::string, double> joint_values;
451  joint_values["base_joint/x"] = 1.0;
452  joint_values["base_joint/y"] = 1.0;
453  joint_values["base_joint/theta"] = 0.5;
454  joint_values["joint_a"] = -0.5;
455  joint_values["joint_c"] = 0.08;
456  state.setVariablePositions(joint_values);
457 
458  EXPECT_NEAR_TRACED(state.getGlobalLinkTransform("base_link").translation(), Eigen::Vector3d(1, 1, 0));
459  EXPECT_NEAR(0.0, Eigen::Quaterniond(state.getGlobalLinkTransform("base_link").linear()).x(), 1e-5);
460  EXPECT_NEAR(0.0, Eigen::Quaterniond(state.getGlobalLinkTransform("base_link").linear()).y(), 1e-5);
461  EXPECT_NEAR(0.247404, Eigen::Quaterniond(state.getGlobalLinkTransform("base_link").linear()).z(), 1e-5);
462  EXPECT_NEAR(0.968912, Eigen::Quaterniond(state.getGlobalLinkTransform("base_link").linear()).w(), 1e-5);
463 
464  EXPECT_NEAR_TRACED(state.getGlobalLinkTransform("link_a").translation(), Eigen::Vector3d(1, 1, 0));
465  EXPECT_NEAR(0.0, Eigen::Quaterniond(state.getGlobalLinkTransform("link_a").linear()).x(), 1e-5);
466  EXPECT_NEAR(0.0, Eigen::Quaterniond(state.getGlobalLinkTransform("link_a").linear()).y(), 1e-5);
467  EXPECT_NEAR(0.0, Eigen::Quaterniond(state.getGlobalLinkTransform("link_a").linear()).z(), 1e-5);
468  EXPECT_NEAR(1.0, Eigen::Quaterniond(state.getGlobalLinkTransform("link_a").linear()).w(), 1e-5);
469 
470  EXPECT_NEAR_TRACED(state.getGlobalLinkTransform("link_b").translation(), Eigen::Vector3d(1, 1.5, 0));
471  EXPECT_NEAR(0.0, Eigen::Quaterniond(state.getGlobalLinkTransform("link_b").linear()).x(), 1e-5);
472  EXPECT_NEAR(-0.2084598, Eigen::Quaterniond(state.getGlobalLinkTransform("link_b").linear()).y(), 1e-5);
473  EXPECT_NEAR(0.0, Eigen::Quaterniond(state.getGlobalLinkTransform("link_b").linear()).z(), 1e-5);
474  EXPECT_NEAR(0.97803091, Eigen::Quaterniond(state.getGlobalLinkTransform("link_b").linear()).w(), 1e-5);
475 
476  EXPECT_NEAR_TRACED(state.getGlobalLinkTransform("link_c").translation(), Eigen::Vector3d(1.08, 1.4, 0));
477  EXPECT_NEAR(0.0, Eigen::Quaterniond(state.getGlobalLinkTransform("link_c").linear()).x(), 1e-5);
478  EXPECT_NEAR(0.0, Eigen::Quaterniond(state.getGlobalLinkTransform("link_c").linear()).y(), 1e-5);
479  EXPECT_NEAR(0.0, Eigen::Quaterniond(state.getGlobalLinkTransform("link_c").linear()).z(), 1e-5);
480  EXPECT_NEAR(1.0, Eigen::Quaterniond(state.getGlobalLinkTransform("link_c").linear()).w(), 1e-5);
481 
482  EXPECT_TRUE(state.satisfiesBounds());
483 
484  std::map<std::string, double> upd_a;
485  upd_a["joint_a"] = 0.2;
486  state.setVariablePositions(upd_a);
487  EXPECT_TRUE(state.satisfiesBounds(model->getJointModel("joint_a")));
488  EXPECT_NEAR(state.getVariablePosition("joint_a"), 0.2, 1e-3);
489  state.enforceBounds();
490  EXPECT_NEAR(state.getVariablePosition("joint_a"), 0.2, 1e-3);
491 
492  upd_a["joint_a"] = 3.2;
493  state.setVariablePositions(upd_a);
494  EXPECT_TRUE(state.satisfiesBounds(model->getJointModel("joint_a")));
495  EXPECT_NEAR(state.getVariablePosition("joint_a"), 3.2, 1e-3);
496  state.enforceBounds();
497  EXPECT_NEAR(state.getVariablePosition("joint_a"), -3.083185, 1e-3);
498  EXPECT_TRUE(state.satisfiesBounds(model->getJointModel("joint_a")));
499 
500  // mimic joints
501  state.setToDefaultValues();
502  EXPECT_TRUE(state.dirtyLinkTransforms());
503  EXPECT_NEAR_TRACED(state.getGlobalLinkTransform("link_c").translation(), Eigen::Vector3d(0.0, 0.4, 0));
504  EXPECT_NEAR_TRACED(state.getGlobalLinkTransform("link_d").translation(), Eigen::Vector3d(0.2, 0.5, 0));
505  EXPECT_NEAR_TRACED(state.getGlobalLinkTransform("link_e").translation(), Eigen::Vector3d(0.3, 0.6, 0));
506 
507  // setVariablePosition should update corresponding mimic joints too
508  state.setVariablePosition("joint_f", 1.0);
509  EXPECT_EQ(state.getVariablePosition("joint_f"), 1.0);
510  EXPECT_EQ(state.getVariablePosition("mim_f"), 1.6);
511  EXPECT_TRUE(state.dirtyLinkTransforms());
512  EXPECT_NEAR_TRACED(state.getGlobalLinkTransform("link_c").translation(), Eigen::Vector3d(0.0, 0.4, 0));
513  EXPECT_NEAR_TRACED(state.getGlobalLinkTransform("link_d").translation(), Eigen::Vector3d(1.7, 0.5, 0));
514  EXPECT_NEAR_TRACED(state.getGlobalLinkTransform("link_e").translation(), Eigen::Vector3d(2.8, 0.6, 0));
515 
516  ASSERT_EQ(g_mim->getVariableCount(), 2u);
517  double gstate[2];
518  state.copyJointGroupPositions(g_mim, gstate);
519 
520  // setToRandomPositions() uses a different mechanism to update mimic joints
521  state.setToRandomPositions(g_mim);
522  double joint_f = state.getVariablePosition("joint_f");
523  double mim_f = state.getVariablePosition("mim_f");
524  EXPECT_NEAR(mim_f, 1.5 * joint_f + 0.1, 1e-8);
525  EXPECT_TRUE(state.dirtyLinkTransforms());
526  EXPECT_NEAR_TRACED(state.getGlobalLinkTransform("link_c").translation(), Eigen::Vector3d(0.0, 0.4, 0));
527  EXPECT_NEAR_TRACED(state.getGlobalLinkTransform("link_d").translation(), Eigen::Vector3d(0.1 + mim_f, 0.5, 0));
528  EXPECT_NEAR_TRACED(state.getGlobalLinkTransform("link_e").translation(),
529  Eigen::Vector3d(0.1 + mim_f + joint_f + 0.1, 0.6, 0));
530 
531  // setJointGroupPositions() uses a different mechanism to update mimic joints
532  state.setJointGroupPositions(g_mim, gstate);
533  EXPECT_EQ(state.getVariablePosition("joint_f"), 1.0);
534  EXPECT_EQ(state.getVariablePosition("mim_f"), 1.6);
535  EXPECT_TRUE(state.dirtyLinkTransforms());
536  EXPECT_NEAR_TRACED(state.getGlobalLinkTransform("link_c").translation(), Eigen::Vector3d(0.0, 0.4, 0));
537  EXPECT_NEAR_TRACED(state.getGlobalLinkTransform("link_d").translation(), Eigen::Vector3d(1.7, 0.5, 0));
538  EXPECT_NEAR_TRACED(state.getGlobalLinkTransform("link_e").translation(), Eigen::Vector3d(2.8, 0.6, 0));
539 }

569 TEST_F(OneRobot, testInterpolation)
570 {
571  moveit::core::RobotState state_a(robot_model_);
572 
573  // Interpolate with itself
574  state_a.setToDefaultValues();
575  moveit::core::RobotState state_b(state_a);
576  moveit::core::RobotState interpolated_state(state_a);
577  for (size_t i = 0; i <= 10; ++i)
578  {
579  state_a.interpolate(state_b, static_cast<double>(i) / 10., interpolated_state,
580  robot_model_->getJointModelGroup("base_from_base_to_e"));
581  EXPECT_NEAR(state_a.distance(state_b), 0, EPSILON)
582  << "Interpolation between identical states yielded a different state.";
583 
584  for (const auto& link_name : robot_model_->getLinkModelNames())
585  {
586  EXPECT_FALSE(interpolated_state.getCollisionBodyTransform(link_name, 0).matrix().hasNaN())
587  << "Interpolation between identical states yielded NaN value.";
588  }
589  }
590 
591  // Some simple interpolation
592  std::map<std::string, double> joint_values;
593  joint_values["base_joint/x"] = 1.0;
594  joint_values["base_joint/y"] = 1.0;
595  state_a.setVariablePositions(joint_values);
596  joint_values["base_joint/x"] = 0.0;
597  joint_values["base_joint/y"] = 2.0;
598  state_b.setVariablePositions(joint_values);
599  EXPECT_NEAR(3 * std::sqrt(2), state_a.distance(state_b), EPSILON) << "Simple interpolation of base_joint failed.";
600 
601  state_a.interpolate(state_b, 0.5, interpolated_state, robot_model_->getJointModelGroup("base_from_base_to_e"));
602  EXPECT_NEAR(0., state_a.distance(interpolated_state) - state_b.distance(interpolated_state), EPSILON)
603  << "Simple interpolation of base_joint failed.";
604  EXPECT_NEAR(0.5, interpolated_state.getVariablePosition("base_joint/x"), EPSILON)
605  << "Simple interpolation of base_joint failed.";
606  EXPECT_NEAR(1.5, interpolated_state.getVariablePosition("base_joint/y"), EPSILON)
607  << "Simple interpolation of base_joint failed.";
608  state_a.interpolate(state_b, 0.1, interpolated_state, robot_model_->getJointModelGroup("base_from_base_to_e"));
609  EXPECT_NEAR(0.9, interpolated_state.getVariablePosition("base_joint/x"), EPSILON)
610  << "Simple interpolation of base_joint failed.";
611  EXPECT_NEAR(1.1, interpolated_state.getVariablePosition("base_joint/y"), EPSILON)
612  << "Simple interpolation of base_joint failed.";
613 
614  // Interpolate all the joints
615  joint_values["base_joint/x"] = 0.0;
616  joint_values["base_joint/y"] = 20.0;
617  joint_values["base_joint/theta"] = 3 * M_PI / 4;
618  joint_values["joint_a"] = -4 * M_PI / 5;
619  joint_values["joint_c"] = 0.0;
620  joint_values["joint_f"] = 1.0;
621  state_a.setVariablePositions(joint_values);
622 
623  joint_values["base_joint/x"] = 10.0;
624  joint_values["base_joint/y"] = 0.0;
625  joint_values["base_joint/theta"] = -3 * M_PI / 4;
626  joint_values["joint_a"] = 4 * M_PI / 5;
627  joint_values["joint_c"] = 0.07;
628  joint_values["joint_f"] = 0.0;
629  state_b.setVariablePositions(joint_values);
630 
631  for (size_t i = 0; i <= 5; ++i)
632  {
633  double t = static_cast<double>(i) / 5.;
634  state_a.interpolate(state_b, t, interpolated_state, robot_model_->getJointModelGroup("base_from_base_to_e"));
635  EXPECT_NEAR(10.0 * t, interpolated_state.getVariablePosition("base_joint/x"), EPSILON)
636  << "Base joint interpolation failed.";
637  EXPECT_NEAR(20.0 * (1 - t), interpolated_state.getVariablePosition("base_joint/y"), EPSILON)
638  << "Base joint interpolation failed.";
639  if (t < 0.5)
640  {
641  EXPECT_NEAR(3 * M_PI / 4 + (M_PI / 2) * t, interpolated_state.getVariablePosition("base_joint/theta"), EPSILON)
642  << "Base joint theta interpolation failed.";
643  EXPECT_NEAR(-4 * M_PI / 5 - (2 * M_PI / 5) * t, interpolated_state.getVariablePosition("joint_a"), EPSILON)
644  << "Continuous joint interpolation failed.";
645  }
646  else
647  {
648  EXPECT_NEAR(-3 * M_PI / 4 - (M_PI / 2) * (1 - t), interpolated_state.getVariablePosition("base_joint/theta"),
649  EPSILON)
650  << "Base joint theta interpolation failed.";
651  EXPECT_NEAR(4 * M_PI / 5 + (2 * M_PI / 5) * (1 - t), interpolated_state.getVariablePosition("joint_a"), EPSILON)
652  << "Continuous joint interpolation failed.";
653  }
654  EXPECT_NEAR(0.07 * t, interpolated_state.getVariablePosition("joint_c"), EPSILON)
655  << "Interpolation of joint_c failed.";
656  EXPECT_NEAR(1 - t, interpolated_state.getVariablePosition("joint_f"), EPSILON)
657  << "Interpolation of joint_f failed.";
658  EXPECT_NEAR(1.5 * (1 - t) + 0.1, interpolated_state.getVariablePosition("mim_f"), EPSILON)
659  << "Interpolation of mimic joint mim_f failed.";
660  }
661 
662  bool nan_exception = false;
663  try
664  {
665  const double infty = std::numeric_limits<double>::infinity();
666  state_a.interpolate(state_b, infty, interpolated_state, robot_model_->getJointModelGroup("base_from_base_to_e"));
667  }
668  catch (std::exception& e)
669  {
670  std::cout << "Caught expected exception: " << e.what() << std::endl;
671  nan_exception = true;
672  }
673  EXPECT_TRUE(nan_exception) << "NaN interpolation parameter did not create expected exception.";
674 }
